text: Goodedulla is a national park in Queensland, Australia, northwest of Brisbane. The park is located in the centre of the Brigalow Belt. Access to the park is by four-wheel-drive vehicle only. Camping requires a permit and is available at three locations; Wadlow Yards, Kings Dam and The Palms, although none of the three have any facilities. ==See also== * Protected areas of Queensland ==References== Category:National parks of Central Queensland Category:Protected areas established in 1994
title: Goodedulla National Park
